timeline.bodyText:
Thinking about this, I think the better implementation is to do this:
if (result == null) {
   return null;
}
else if (Order.TEST_ORDER_TYPE_UUID.equals(result.getOrderType().getUuid()))) {
    return (TestOrder) result;
}
else {
    throw new FhirException("UUID is not a valid Test Order");
}
But we might also get the correct behaviour much more simply by doing this:
return (TestOrder) sessionFactory.getCurrentSession().createCriteria(TestOrder.class).add(Restrictions.eq("uuid", uuid)).uniqueResult();
Though I'm not 100% sure that would work given the inheritance.

